Rating: 3
Delicious! I used Yukon Gold potatoes and riced 'em rather than mashing -- lovely consistency. I eyeballed the half and half and probably put a little less than 1.5 cups based on the watery results of others. It was fine, but I think it would have been fine doing the entire recipe. I did add two small heads of roasted garlic, but no garlic flavor really came through. Next time, I will slow cook the garlic in the butter and then add the mixture for a more powerful flavor. The rosemary flavor really does come through -- it's subtle but absolutely lovely.

