Rating: 3
Ok, here's the exciting thing about this recipe: you can do almost ANYTHING with it. You can leave it as is, you can add garlic, chives--there are SO many options! This is the perfect basic mashed potatoes recipe. I cut the potatoes into 1" cubes and cooked them for about 20 minutes (until nice and tender), then blended them with the butter and rosemary in a mixer. After I was sure the butter was incorporated I mixed the cream until it was nice and fluffy (oh YUM!), and lastly I scooped individual servings into ramkins and baked until the tops were golden brown. El YUMMO!

Rating: 3
A good, solid, flavorful recipe that makes a good backdrop for spicier foods. Not every dish on a menu should blow out one's tastebuds...something has to play the low notes. For those of us who like more texture in our foods, though, don't bother to peel the potatoes. Just scrub them well and mix the nutritious peeling right into the dish.

